canonical:
  title: 送李林宗直郞歸舊隱
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 我欲歸歟久未歸君胡去矣復來斯衣冠恰似倡優戲升斗爭敎妻子肥却羡已收匡國策自憐苦乏買山貲百年後有知音在不用題詩淚滿衣
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 送李林宗直郞歸舊隱
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 我欲歸歟久未歸。君胡去矣復來斯。衣冠恰似倡優戲。升斗爭敎妻子肥。却羡已收匡國策。自憐苦乏買山貲。百年後有知音在。不用題詩淚滿衣。
korean:
  title: 옛 마을로 돌아가 숨는 이림종 직랑을 보내며
  author: 최해
  language: kor
  text: |-
    나도 돌아가려 하나, 오래도록 못 돌아가는데
    그대는 어이 가다가 다시 왔는고
    의관은 흡사 이까짓 배우의 차림새
    쌀 몇 말 녹으로 다투어 어찌 처자를 살찌게 하리
    부러워라, 그대는 나랏일 다하고 가네만
    불쌍한 나는 산 살 밑천도 없네그려
    아서라, 백 년 뒤엔 지음이 있으리니
    시 쓸 때에 눈물 흘려 옷 적셔서 무엇하리
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0180_010_0070&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 산(山) 살 밑천 : '
    value: 진(晉)나라 중 지도림(支道林)이 심공(深公)에게 숨어살 산을 사달라고 부탁한 일이 있었다.
english:
  title: Sending Off Li Linzong, a Gentleman of the Secretariat, as He Returns to His Old Hermitage
  author: Choe Hae
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I too have longed to return, yet return I have not after all these years.
    How is it you depart, only to come back again?
    Our robes and caps are but the costumes of strolling players—
    We squabble over a few measures of rice to fatten wife and child.

    I envy you, who have completed your service to the state and go,
    While I, poor soul, lack even the means to buy a mountain home.
    But take heart—a hundred years hence, there will be those who understand.
    Why then should you weep and soak your sleeves with tears when writing poems?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The phrase 'means to buy a mountain home' alludes to the historical figure Zhi Daolin of the Jin dynasty, who asked his teacher Shen Gong to help him find a mountain retreat where he might live as a hermit—a symbol of withdrawal from worldly affairs.
